To complete this assignment, you can follow the steps below to build a simple Todo application. I'll provide an outline and example code snippets for each step.

. Backend Setup
We'll use Node.js with Express for setting up the backend API. You can store the todos in an in-memory array or MongoDB. Here's an example of both.

step-nstall Dependencies
npm init -y
npm install express mongoose body-parser cors nodemon

step-"scripts": {
  "start": "node index.js",
  "dev": "nodemon index.js"
}
